<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="32.[227,348,1884,1910]" box="[227,348,1884,1910]" pageId="32" pageNumber="42">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,348,1884,1910]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="32" pageNumber="42" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,348,1884,1910]" pageId="32" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[227,1437,1930,2063]" pageId="32" pageNumber="42">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hyatt" authorityYear="1900" box="[362,566,1930,1956]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Acanthoclymeniidae" genus="Acanthoclymenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="32" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[362,566,1930,1956]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="42">Acanthoclymenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reaching about 
<quantity box="[762,848,1931,1957]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
conch diameter with small, extremely discoidal, evolute conch between12 and 32 dm (uw/dm decreasing from ~ 0.50 to ~ 0.45). Whorl profile compressed; umbilical wall shallow and rounded, whorl profile pear-shaped, ventrolateral margin angular, venter flat. Growth lines very fine, strongly biconvex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
